### ============================================
### 📝 TESTING NOTES
### ============================================
###
### PUBLIC ROUTES (No authentication):
### - GET /reservations/availability (check free tables)
###
### CUSTOMER ROUTES (Requires customer token):
### - POST /reservations (create booking)
### - GET /reservations/my-reservations (view my bookings)
### - GET /reservations/:id (view specific booking - must own it)
### - PATCH /reservations/:id/cancel (cancel my booking)
###
### ADMIN ROUTES (Requires admin token):
### - GET /reservations/admin/all (view all bookings)
### - PATCH /reservations/admin/:id/status (change booking status)
###
### RESERVATION STATUS LIFECYCLE:
### 1. pending (default when created)
### 2. confirmed (admin confirms)
### 3. completed (customer showed up)
### 4. cancelled (customer cancelled)
### 5. no-show (customer didn't show up)
###
### TRANSACTION PROTECTION:
### - Double booking is prevented using MongoDB transactions
### - If two users try to book same table simultaneously, only one succeeds
###
